---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="AI Toolkit | Willy W."
  description="The AI tools Willy W. uses to plan, build, review, and remember work."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <p class="kicker">toolkit</p>
    <h1>The tools are not the story. The workflow is.</h1>
    <p>
      This page will become a practical map of how I divide work between models, tools, and
      durable notes. For now, it keeps the structure ready.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section aria-labelledby="tool-list-title">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <h2 id="tool-list-title">Stack</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="page-stack">
      <article class="page-card">
        <h3>Claude</h3>
        <p>
          Used for architecture, critique, review, and judgment-heavy planning. The job is to
          make the plan sharper before code exists.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="page-card">
        <h3>Codex</h3>
        <p>
          Used for implementation, verification, and local iteration. The job is to turn a scoped
          prompt into working files and repeatable checks.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="page-card">
        <h3>Obsidian</h3>
        <p>
          Used as project memory. Decisions, notes, and handoffs live outside chat so the next
          session starts from facts, not vibes.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
